FINAL MESSAGE TO SEND DEVELOPERS

Copy this:

Important Update (Kafka SSL Connection)

Please stop using the .p12 certificates (cluster-ca-cert.p12 and clients-ca-cert.p12).
These CAs do not match the Kafka Route on port 443 and will always cause:

SSLHandshakeException
PKIX path building failed


Kafka external listener on OpenShift uses OpenShift Router CA, not Strimzi CA.

Use the following SSL configuration:

properties:
  security.protocol: SSL
ssl:
  truststore:
    location: C:/certs/kafka/ca.crt
    type: PEM


Where ca.crt is extracted from:

ConfigMap: kube-root-ca.crt
Namespace: dev-kafka


No keystore and no password are required.
